WEBVTT

00:04.838 --> 00:06.465
<i>Talking with Silicon Valley...</i>

00:07.508 --> 00:10.844
<i>the tech world, because
they're like, "Food, come on.</i>

00:10.844 --> 00:13.597
"Like, you know, we create AI,

00:13.597 --> 00:17.726
"you know, we create smartphones,
we put fucking satellites in space.

00:17.726 --> 00:20.646
This is low‐brow shit.
We can do this like that."

00:23.190 --> 00:28.487
<i>I remember talking with
one of NASA's chief engineers about food.</i>

00:28.487 --> 00:32.074
<i>This asshole tells me,
"I can recreate your cooking intuition."</i>

00:32.741 --> 00:37.037
<i>That was the general sort of sentiment
from the tech world,</i>

00:37.037 --> 00:42.709
<i>that food and the creation of food
was a fucking zero, one.</i>

00:42.709 --> 00:44.086
<i>It was a binary thing.</i>

00:45.254 --> 00:47.714
<i>We could be replaced.
We could be automated.</i>

00:48.590 --> 00:51.468
<i>And it could be scaled very quickly.</i>

00:52.928 --> 00:55.055
<i>They just believe that they could.</i>

00:56.223 --> 01:01.520
<i>Technology has fundamentally altered
the restaurant industry,</i>

01:01.520 --> 01:03.522
<i>and I don't know if we're prepared for it.</i>

01:04.898 --> 01:06.567
<i>All the shit was gonna happen,</i>

01:06.567 --> 01:09.361
<i>but you never would have heard
about it in the news</i>

01:09.361 --> 01:12.155
<i>because it would have happened
over a long period of time.</i>

01:13.949 --> 01:15.075
It's been a while.

01:15.075 --> 01:18.161
<i>Growing concern
over a growing health crisis.</i>

01:18.161 --> 01:21.206
‐ Over a million
have now been infected by coronavirus.

01:21.206 --> 01:23.208
‐ Stay at home.
That is the order tonight.

01:23.208 --> 01:25.294
‐ Restaurants have taken a hard hit.

01:26.253 --> 01:29.464
<i>It would have been like
that biology experiment in high school</i>

01:29.464 --> 01:32.801
where you plop a fucking frog
in‐‐ in water

01:32.801 --> 01:35.971
<i>and you increase the temperature
every five minutes or so.</i>

01:35.971 --> 01:39.016
<i>And it boils itself. Doesn't even know.</i>

01:39.016 --> 01:41.018
But if you change
the temperature immediately,

01:41.018 --> 01:42.019
frog's gonna know,

01:42.019 --> 01:43.812
and that's what's happened right now.

01:45.397 --> 01:47.858
<i>The change of automation,
it's fucking here.</i>

01:48.567 --> 01:51.153
<i>The best way I've come to understand
where food is going</i>

01:51.153 --> 01:52.529
<i>is by looking at delivery.</i>

01:53.030 --> 01:55.991
<i>The future is convenience
across the board.</i>

01:57.201 --> 02:00.204
<i>But what's the cost of convenience?</i>

02:01.622 --> 02:03.624
♪ theme music playing ♪

02:10.464 --> 02:13.175
<i>♪ Born in Gossip County ♪</i>

02:13.926 --> 02:16.386
<i>♪ In Big Mouth, USA... ♪</i>

02:17.054 --> 02:19.890
‐ More Americans
are ordering takeout these days

02:19.890 --> 02:22.267
