He's ordering
from multiple Vietnamese restaurants.

05:07.933 --> 05:10.060
‐ Yeah. You haven't done that?

05:10.060 --> 05:11.478
‐ That is next, next level.

05:11.478 --> 05:13.438
I don't have enough credit cards
to, like, handle all the‐‐

05:13.438 --> 05:14.940
Yeah, it's too many apps.

05:14.940 --> 05:17.276
‐ But when you described that,
you have that sense of wonderment

05:17.276 --> 05:21.029
'cause I think we all grew up
not having this level of convenience.

05:21.029 --> 05:22.531
And we're like, "Woah!"

05:22.531 --> 05:24.491
Like, my kids will never know that, like,

05:24.491 --> 05:26.827
there was a time when you couldn't
just tap on your phone and get it.

05:26.827 --> 05:28.203
Right.
‐ Right.

05:37.087 --> 05:40.757
<i>There were many reasons why we
didn't want to do delivery at Momofuku.</i>

05:42.009 --> 05:45.387
<i>We figured out most of the foods
that we make don't deliver well.</i>

05:45.387 --> 05:49.725
There were a lot of chefs,
almost everyone I seemed to know,

05:49.725 --> 05:51.768
being like, "What are you doing?

05:51.768 --> 05:54.188
<i>"You're so stupid. Just do delivery.</i>

05:54.188 --> 05:56.106
<i>"All these Chinese restaurants
do delivery.</i>

05:56.106 --> 05:59.151
<i>You make Asian food.
What the fuck are you doing?"</i>

05:59.151 --> 06:01.111
We tested it out. Didn't travel well.

06:01.111 --> 06:03.405
Hot noodle soups doesn't travel.

06:04.281 --> 06:06.992
<i>We studied it and studied it
and studied it.</i>

06:06.992 --> 06:10.162
We came up with a menu
of foods that delivered well.

06:14.249 --> 06:16.251
<i>I started two companies.</i>

06:16.251 --> 06:17.544
<i>Maple was healthy,</i>

06:17.544 --> 06:20.923
<i>and Ando
was all relatively unhealthy foods.</i>

06:22.007 --> 06:23.967
<i>It was to be a full‐stack operation.</i>

06:23.967 --> 06:26.512
<i>So we would own the couriers,</i>

06:26.512 --> 06:30.432
<i>the logistics, the technology,
and the production of food</i>

06:30.432 --> 06:32.518
<i>in one‐stop shop.</i>

06:32.518 --> 06:34.436
<i>The app, I thought, was amazing.</i>

06:34.436 --> 06:38.982
<i>And there was a giant commissary,
and it worked!</i>

06:38.982 --> 06:41.360
<i>I mean, we were doing some crazy numbers.</i>

06:41.360 --> 06:45.197
<i>But it's incredibly difficult
to actually pull something like this off.</i>

06:45.197 --> 06:46.823
<i>And I got the timing wrong.</i>

06:47.658 --> 06:52.329
I think most of my best ideas
about food, um,

06:52.329 --> 06:53.413
have been right

06:53.413 --> 06:56.625
<i>but wrong on timing,
but ultimately, timing is everything.</i>

07:02.422 --> 07:04.007
<i>We missed our window,</i>

07:04.007 --> 07:06.844
<i>and now the apps are here
and are only getting bigger.</i>

07:08.512 --> 07:10.639
‐ You want people
to not use delivery services?

07:10.639 --> 07:13.350
‐ No. The‐‐ the model has to be better.

07:13.350 --> 07:16.979
It will eradicate the mom‐and‐pop
and the mid‐market restaurant.

07:16.979 --> 07:20.065
I want to be hopeful.
I don't know how to preserve that.

07:21.733 --> 07:24.903
<i>Independent restaurants,
if you look at nature documentaries,</i>

07:24.903 --> 07:26.154
we're the prey.

07:29.241 --> 07:30.993
<i>Let's just say someone orders,
let's just say,</i>

07:30.993 --> 07:32.995
<i>$100 worth of food
from a restaurant.</i>

07:34.955 --> 07:37.541
<i>The delivery company
takes about $30 of that.</i>

07:38.959 --> 07:41.628
<i>About 30% right off the top.</i>

07:43.297 --> 07:45.007
<i>"That's it. That's mine."</i>

07:47.134 --> 07:51.388
You know, restaurant business
where your margins for profitability

07:51.388 --> 07:53.390
are often negative,

07:53.390 --> 07:54.516
<i>it's a problem.</i>

07:54.516 --> 07:56.101
<i>Because I don't even know
if these delivery companies</i>

07:56.101 --> 07:57.978
<i>are making money
to begin with now, right?</i>

07:57.978 --> 08:00.063
<i>It seems like everyone
is losing money on this.</i>

08:00.063 --> 08:01.648
<i>We should start by acknowledging</i>

08:01.648 --> 08:03.692
<i>that today Uber Eats
does not make money.</i>

